Bielik: &quot;I was hoping that I would get a chance under Unai Emery but it turned out that he couldn't see me in his plans. I don't want to say it's a shame now. I love #Arsenal &amp; playing for this club was my dream. However, it was necessary to stray from this path&quot;<br />
<br />
Bielik: &quot;I came to the club from the Championship, where I will play &amp; gain experience. I think that after the next season, if I play regularly, I will be ready for the Premier League&quot;

Arsenal youngster Eddie Nketiah has enjoyed an explosive start to the season, scoring three goals at the start of his loan spell with Leeds and bagging a brace for the England under-21s in Turkey on Friday night. However, the striker has revealed he ignored the request of Arsenal coach Unai Emery for him to stay at the Emirates in favour of first-team football out on loan for 2019-20.<br />
<br />
&quot;The manager wanted me to stay so it's really confidence-boosting for me that he had me in his plans,&quot; Nketiah said. &quot;But I felt like it was a good step for me to come to Leeds. I hope it's a good year that can leave me in good stead going back to Arsenal to fight for a place. There were a lot of options, there were options for me to go to Germany but me, my family and the club decided Leeds was the best place.&quot;

Umtiti on summer #Arsenal rumours: &quot;Honestly, I don&rsquo;t know where this rumour with Arsenal came from. Overnight, I received messages from my friends &lsquo;ah, so you are joining Arsenal?&rsquo; I&rsquo;m not, I&rsquo;m sorry but I&rsquo;m staying at Barcelona&quot;<br />
<br />
Umtiti: &quot;Contacts with #Arsenal? To be honest, I don't know if they had conversations with my agent, I just told him I didn't care what was happening this summer &amp; that it wasn't even necessary to talk to me about it. My dream as a child is to play for Barcelona&quot;

Give Mesut Ozil a run of 5 games in the side and see what he can do. I've seen players like Mkhitaryan given chance after chance despite playing awful. Ozil at #10 with our front 3 would be a thing of beauty.<br />
<br />
@ltarsenal

